Usage: taup curve [--debug] [--help] [--xlog] [--ylog] [--mapwidth=<mapwidth>]
                  [--mapwidthunit=<mapWidthUnit>] [-o=<outFile>]
                  [--prop=<toolPropsFilename>] [--reddeg=<reduceVelDeg>]
                  [--redkm=<reduceVelKm>] [--rel=<relativePhaseName>]
                  [-x=<xAxisType>] [-y=<yAxisType>] [-p=<phaseNames>[,
                  <phaseNames>...]]... [--xminmax=x x]... [--yminmax=y y]...
                  [[-mod=<modelname>] [-h=<sourceDepth>] [--stadepth=depth]
                  [--scat=s s]...] [--text | --json | --gmt | --svg]
plot traveltime and other curves for phases
      --debug              display debugging message
      --help               display this help message
      --mapwidth=<mapwidth>
                           plot width in inches for GMT, pixels for SVG.
      --mapwidthunit=<mapWidthUnit>
                           plot width unit for GMT. Default is i for inchs
  -o, --output=<outFile>   output to file, default is stdout.
  -p, --ph, --phase=<phaseNames>[,<phaseNames>...]
                           seismic phase names
      --prop=<toolPropsFilename>
                           load defaults from properties file
      --reddeg=<reduceVelDeg>
                           outputs curves with a reducing velocity (deg/sec),
                             no effect if axis is not distance-like/time
      --redkm=<reduceVelKm>
                           outputs curves with a reducing velocity (km/sec), no
                             effect if axis is not distance-like/time
      --rel=<relativePhaseName>
                           plot relative to the given phase, no effect unless
                             distance/time
  -x=<xAxisType>           X axis data type, one of radian, radian_pi, degree,
                             degree_180, kilometer, kilometer_180, rayparam,
                             time, tau, turndepth, amp, amppsv, ampsh,
                             geospread, refltran, refltranpsv, refltransh,
                             index, theta
      --xlog               X axis is log
      --xminmax=x x        min and max x axis for plotting
  -y=<yAxisType>           Y axis data type, one of radian, radian_pi, degree,
                             degree_180, kilometer, kilometer_180, rayparam,
                             time, tau, turndepth, amp, amppsv, ampsh,
                             geospread, refltran, refltranpsv, refltransh,
                             index, theta
      --ylog               Y axis is log
      --yminmax=y y        min and max y axis for plotting
Model Args
  -h, --sourcedepth=<sourceDepth>
                           source depth in km
      -mod, --mod, --model=<modelname>
                           use velocity model "modelname" for calculations
                                                 Default is iasp91.
      --scat, --scatter=s s
                           scattering depth and distance in degrees, which may
                             be negative.
      --stadepth=depth     the receiver depth in km for stations not at the
                             surface
Output Type
      --gmt                outputs as GMT
      --json               outputs as JSON
      --svg                outputs as SVG
      --text               outputs as text
